StressorDesc:
Recently, I learned that my company was no longer providing weekly covid tests. I work at an agency that manages group homes. While they said it was because of new CDC guidelines, the real reason was that too many staff were testing positive and being sent home. If a staff was asymptomatic or working in a house that had already been exposed, they wanted them to keep working. Otherwise, we could not maintain our legal ratio and would have no caregivers.

During the high point of the omicron surge, I had to work 55 hours in a row without leaving because all other staff for my house had covid. As soon as those staff had passed their 5 day mark since their positive test, the company wanted them back at work.

I felt such a blatant disregard for our safety, and the safety of the individuals we serve. I was upset with the company for failing to adequately staff their houses. We are underpaid and I do not blame people for leaving the company. They are not providing enough support or incentives for their workers.
